cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper analyzes the long-term statistics of queries to websites using logs collected on web caches, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also discusses the sensitivity of the statistics to different parameters, which could be relevant to the social and information networks (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SD) sub-categories. The proposed modification of the Zipf law could be relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) and cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories.
